description.p: This field contains Contains the PCIe Requester ID (RID) header field value used in PCIe requests generated due to this message.

This field contains Contains the PCIe TLP Processing Hints Present (TH) header field value used in PCIe requests generated due to this message, and is used to indicate the presence of the Processing Hints (PH) and Steering Tag (ST) in the TLP header and, if enabled, the . The presence of the optional TPH TLP Prefix.

This field contains Contains the PCIe TLP Digest (TD) header field value used in PCIe requests generated due to this message and controls the generation of the TLP digest in PCIe requests generated due to this message.
When this bit is set to one 1, a TLP prefix is prepended perpended to all PCIe requests generated due to this message.
When the PCIe TLP Processing Hints Present (TH) bit is set in the message, this field contains the Steering Tag (ST) field used in PCIe requests generated due to this message.
If the TH bit in cleared in the message, then the value of this field has no effect on message processing.

Bit 0 of this field corresponds : Corresponds to TLP prefix byte 3 bit 0.
Bit 8 of this field corresponds : Corresponds to TLP prefix byte 2 bit 0.
Bit 16 of this field corresponds : Corresponds to TLP prefix byte 1 bit 0.
Bit 28 of this field corresponds : Corresponds to TLP prefix Type field bit 4.
